<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="01e11485-9ee5-5bb2-847c-eafeb0db2e37" activityNameId="a7ba3566-691d-4272-80cd-3fe32846c3bc" parentActivityId="c8a75fa3-1ee8-4e7c-8695-c4bc57a63827" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for sodium bicarbonate</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Bicarbonate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Sodium Hydrogen Carbonate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Sodium</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Baking Soda</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Carbonic Acid Monosodium Salt</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Hydrogen Carbonate</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">Activity starts at factory gate, with the finished product ready for transport. </includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity includes the transport of the products to the consumer.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This is the market for 'sodium bicarbonate', in the European geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">The transport amounts are based on eurostat transport statistics for 2016 (http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/data/database, extracted on the 2018-06-01). See exchange comments for additional details.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">'sodium bicarbonate'  is an inorganic substance with a CAS no. : 000144-55-8. It is called 'sodium;hydrogen carbonate' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: CHNaO3. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure , it appears as a white powder and is soluble in water (especially hot water). It is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: cooking, pyrotechnics, disinfectants, fire extinguishers, cleaning agents. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
